Program: Outlook
Title: The 'Living Dead' of India
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03kbqyn
Last Broadcast Date: Not available
A look at the 'living dead' of India, people who have been falsely declared dead by others who then claim their property. Also, Nejla Coskun the Kurdish girl who set fire to herself in protest at the arrest of Abdullah Ocalan; A look at National Anthems; Chef Antonio Carluccio and his love for mushrooms; Insight into Mozart through the discovery of his skull. Finally, the story of Dayne Childs and the dispute over his burial. Presenter: Heather Payton Show less